In [99]:
print("For sex :")
srv=DataFrame[(DataFrame['Survived'] == 1)].select_dtypes(include = 'number')
die=DataFrame[(DataFrame['Survived'] == 0)].select_dtypes(include = 'number')
x = np.arange(-10, 10, 0.0001)
plt.xlabel('Sex')    
plt.ylabel('Survived')
srvPdf = norm.pdf(x,srv['Sex'].mean(),srv['Sex'].std())
diePdf = norm.pdf(x,die['Sex'].mean(),die['Sex'].std())
plt.plot(x, srvPdf,color = 'gold')
plt.plot(x, diePdf,color = 'green')
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle="--")
plt.show()

def probability (feature,meanS,stdS,meanD,stdD):
    return (int(norm.pdf(feature, meanS, stdS) > norm.pdf(feature, meanS, stdS)))
DataFrame2 = pd.read_csv('C:/Users/Asus/Desktop/P-0/test.csv')
DataFrame2['Sex']=DataFrame2['Sex'].replace(to_replace=['male'],value =1)
DataFrame2['Sex']=DataFrame2['Sex'].replace(to_replace=['female'], value =0)
DataFrame2['Survived'] = DataFrame2['Sex'].apply(probability, args=(srv['Sex'].mean(),srv['Sex'].std(),die['Sex'].mean(),die['Sex'].std()))
